        },
        {
          "title": "Key figures forces",
          "body": [
            "The forces shaping the spread are competition, interest rate levels, and credit risk. Competition from other banks pushes deposit rates up and loan rates down, compressing the margin. Rising base rates from the Fed can widen margins if banks raise loan rates faster than deposit rates.",
