          "title": "Core idea",
          "body": [
            "The net interest margin is the percentage difference between the interest a bank earns on its loans and the interest it pays on its deposits and borrowings. A wider margin means more profit per dollar deployed. A narrower margin means the bank has to work harder with the same pool of money.",
